data.title: Acorn, a provider of power generator solutions, to host Q3 earnings call on Nov. 6th at 11am ET. Stock symbol ACFN.
data.description: ACFN will be hosting its Q3 earnings call on Thursday, November 6th at 11am Eastern Time. Acorn, a leading provider of monitoring and control solutions for power generators, will discuss their financial performance during this call. Investors and stakeholders can join the call to learn more about the company's performance in the third quarter. The call will be a key opportunity to gain insights into ACFN's revenue, profits, and strategies moving forward. Interested individuals in the generator and monitoring industry should mark their calendars for this event.

data.title: Arcos and Chef José Andrés collaborate on José Andrés Jamón Knife, honoring Spanish tradition.
data.description: In ALBACETE, Spain, on October 31, 2025, Arcos, renowned as Spain's oldest knife producer with a history spanning almost 300 years, introduces the José Andrés Jamón Knife. This knife pays homage to Spanish traditions, culinary expertise, and the cherished practice of carving jamón ibérico.

data.title: Agnico Eagle Mines reports strong Q3 with $1.06B net income, $1.82B operating cash flow, forms critical minerals subsidiary.
data.description: Agnico Eagle Mines, the world's second-largest gold producer, announced strong third-quarter results along with the formation of a new subsidiary, Avenir Minerals. The firm reported a net income of $1.06 billion, or $2.10 per share, with $1.82 billion in operating cash flow and $1.19 billion in free cash flow. The company attributed the positive results to strong production and higher gold prices. Quarterly production reached 866,936 ounces, led by the Meadowbank and LaRonde mines, with cash costs at $994/oz and all-in sustaining costs at $1,373/oz. President and CEO Ammar Al-Joundi highlighted the company's focus on operational performance, cost management, and productivity to meet full-year production and cost targets.

data.title: Retail investors on Reddit hyped up five stocks including Amazon, Nvidia, Reddit, Beyond Meat, Alphabet. Amazon reported $180.2 billion revenue in Q3 with a 38% profit growth, shares jumping 14%. Nvidia announced U.S. AI infrastructure investments, reached a $5 trillion market cap. Follow the story on Benzinga.com.
data.description: Retail investors on platforms like X and Reddit's r/WallStreetBets were boosting interest in five popular stocks from October 27–31. These included Amazon.com Inc. (AMZN), Nvidia Corp. (NVDA), Reddit Inc. (RDDT), Beyond Meat Inc. (BYND), and Alphabet Inc. (GOOG). Amazon made headlines with strong Q3 earnings, surpassing revenue estimates at $180.2 billion, with a 38% profit growth. AWS performed exceptionally well, leading to a 14% surge in share price after hours trading. The stock was trading around $251 to $252, representing a 1.20% YTD increase and a 19.56% yearly jump. Nvidia, after announcing plans for U.S. AI infrastructure and collaborations for supercomputers with the DOE, experienced a stock surge on Oct. 29, reaching a $5 trillion market cap, a first in history. Further details about Nvidia's performance can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Anthropic presents AI strategy to U.S. Govt, focusing on security, export controls, and energy infra for AI Action Plan.
data.description: Anthropic has submitted comprehensive suggestions to the Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP) regarding the U.S. AI Action Plan. Focus areas include national security, export controls, and energy infrastructure. This move underscores the company's commitment to enhancing AI strategies in the U.S. and maximizing its impact on key sectors. The recommendations aim to bolster the country's AI capabilities and increase its competitive edge in the global market. With this initiative, Anthropic is playing a crucial role in shaping the future of AI policy, ensuring that the nation remains at the forefront of innovation and technology.

data.title: Bending Spoons raised $7.1 billion in equity financing with a pre-money valuation of $110 billion. More than 6 companies participated in the investment, with T. Rowe Price Investment Management providing advice.="'.
data.description: Milan-- Bending Spoons, one of Europe's leading tech companies, announced today that it has raised $710 million in equity, with a pre-money valuation of $11 billion. The transaction was advised by T. Rowe Price Investment Management Co. with participation from Baillie Gifford, Cox Enterprises, Durable Capital Partners, Fidelity Management & Research Company, Foxhaven Asset Management, and Radcliff. Goldman Sachs International served as the exclusive placement agent, and the legal counsel for the deal was provided by High Wins Law Firm. ZNR Notai offered notarial consulting services. Luca Ferrari, co-founder and CEO of Bending Spoons, stated, "This moment is a recognition of the value of our work over the past decade and an important acknowledgement of the achievements we have made at Bending Spoons so far. We are still in the early stages and have ambitious plans for continued investment and growth." "We are proud to have attracted some of the world's best investors who believe in our ability to create value and future opportunities."
